1. Synopsis

   EJTS3ServerQuery library is a free TS3 ServerQuery library. This means that
   it provides you with the possibility to connect to a Teamspeak3 server and
   execute certain ServerQuery commands.
   EJTS3ServerQuery can be used on any platform supporting Java6.
    ___________________________________________________________________________

2. Features

    * Connect to the TS3 ServerQuery Port
    * Select a virtual server and a display name
    * Get various lists from the server. such as
      * server list
      * client list
      * ban list
      * complain list
      * channel list
    * Move one or more clients to another channel
    * Add and delete bans
    * Add and delete complains
    * Add and delete channels
    * ...
    ___________________________________________________________________________

3. Installation

   This library is used by other programs. Therefore please read the README of
   the program using this library for further information.
    ___________________________________________________________________________

3.1. Dependencies

    * Oracle Java6
    * Javadoc
    ___________________________________________________________________________

4. More Information

   This library is a fork of the JTS3ServerQuery library developed by Stefan
   Martens. You can get the original version of the JTS3ServerQuery library at
   http://stefan1200.bplaced.net
    ___________________________________________________________________________

4.1 How to report bugs

   Bugs can be filed as issues at the Github Issue Tracker at
   https://github.com/bb-generation/EJTS3ServerQuery/issues or submitted
   directly to us at bbots@bbgen.net.
    ___________________________________________________________________________

4.2. How to get involved

   If you are a Java developer and would like to help us develope this library
   please take a look at our Github Project at
   https://github.com/bb-generation/EJTS3ServerQuery
   If you have implemented a new feature, just create a new Issue and attach
   your patch to it. Take a look at HACKING for further details.
    ___________________________________________________________________________

